00:19:56.630 --> 00:19:59.240
MAURICE TURNER: Well, I'm just
here in my personal capacity.

00:19:59.240 --> 00:20:03.500
I'm not here representing
where I work or my fellowship.

00:20:03.500 --> 00:20:06.410
And in my role
personally, the way

00:20:06.410 --> 00:20:08.510
that I see it is
just to show people

00:20:08.510 --> 00:20:11.450
that there is a way to
make this change happen.

00:20:11.450 --> 00:20:14.960
There are over 1,400
racist place names.

00:20:14.960 --> 00:20:18.590
There are places like
Dead Negro Hollow

00:20:18.590 --> 00:20:23.340
in Tennessee, Dago Springs,
Chinaman's Hat, Squaw Tit

00:20:23.340 --> 00:20:23.840
Summit.

00:20:23.840 --> 00:20:27.060
And just there are so many
names that are out there.

00:20:27.060 --> 00:20:30.770
So I would just say that
if you come across a name

00:20:30.770 --> 00:20:33.050
when you're out walking
around and enjoying nature

00:20:33.050 --> 00:20:36.866
and you think that that
name needs to be changed,

00:20:36.866 --> 00:20:38.240
there is a process
to go through.

00:20:38.240 --> 00:20:40.040
The change can happen.

00:20:40.040 --> 00:20:41.630
But the only way the
change can happen

00:20:41.630 --> 00:20:45.390
is if someone submits
a proposal and says,

00:20:45.390 --> 00:20:47.390
hey, there's something
wrong with this name,

00:20:47.390 --> 00:20:49.040
here's a better idea.

00:20:49.040 --> 00:20:51.200
Please go ahead and at
least have the discussion

00:20:51.200 --> 00:20:53.270
with the local
community to come up

00:20:53.270 --> 00:20:54.920
with a better name,
something that's

00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:58.030
more reflective of the
community as it is today,

00:20:58.030 --> 00:21:01.790
not as it was in the past,
where derogatory names were

00:21:01.790 --> 00:21:02.635
more acceptable.

00:21:02.635 --> 00:21:04.010
BRANDI: I imagine
there are going

00:21:04.010 --> 00:21:06.301
